         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">June 10 /80 ¶ Dear Mueller ¶  ¶ Thanks many for your notes on Vol. iii. pt. 1 of the Genera. ¶  The omission of Balanops from Rockingham Bay ¶  is unfortunate  ¶  ¶ — also of anthers of Gyrocarpus und...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">80.06.10</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS embossed with crest of Royal Gardens Kew. MS annotation by M: 'Answ 10/8/80'.</p>
               </note>June 10 /80</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thanks many for your notes on Vol. iii. pt. 1 of the Genera.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 25 April 1880.</p>
               </note> The omission of <name key="Balanops">Balanops</name> from Rockingham Bay<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld.</p>
               </note> is unfortunate <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 3, p. 341, say of <name key="Balanops">Balanops</name>eae: 'Species 6 v. 7, omnes Novo-Caledoniceae'.</p>
               </note>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— also of anthers of <name key="Gyrocarpus">Gyrocarpus</name> under the remarks to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Laurineae">Laurineae</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>, but you will find it under the "Genera affinia".<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 3, p. 149.</p>
               </note> —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>"<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Batis">Batis</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Halorageae">Halorageae</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>" — where have you indicated this?<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 10 August 1880.</p>
               </note> I know of no <name key="Halorageae">Halorageae</name> with erect ovules &amp; Exalbuminous seeds, or similar Embryo to that of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Batis">Batis</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Piperacea">Piperacea</name> in N.Z. — &amp; hence Extratropical — observe we say "<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">vix</hi>
               </seg> extra tropicos" which is surely enough. No doubt there are a few also in Extratropical Asia, (Japan even) N. America &amp; S. America.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You say "do you now distinguish only one <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Telopea">Telopea</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>". — we mention 2.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 3, p. 126.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No I do not like Radlkofers Genera of <name key="Sapindaceae">Sapindaceae</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Radlkofer (1875), where the genus is split into many sections; Radlkofer (1879).</p>
               </note> &amp; he seems to have made a species of every collectors specimen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am very much puzzled with the Palms. A trip round the coast &amp; to Lord Howes Island to clear them up would be well worth the time &amp; money. The Australians are in a deplorable state of imperfect descriptions. Can you help me to materials for</p>
